  "content": "Term premium is extra yield demanded for holding long-term bonds vs rolling short-term. Compensates for rate and inflation uncertainty. QE compresses term premiums; QT raises them. Can turn negative (2016-2021), signaling extreme duration demand. Estimated via ACM model.",
